(24, 1, 'Origami Butterfly Instructions and Diagrams', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Butterfly Instructions and Diagrams</h1>\n</header>\n  \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/butterfly/origami-butterfly.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Butterfly\">Origami Butterfly<br>by Atsushi Tajiri<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy-Medium</span></div>\n<p>This origami butterfly is absolutely beautiful and looks even better with nice origami paper. The wings spread out nicely and the body comes up a little to give it a more realistic look. The head adds another dimension of realism and if you like, you can make and attach some antennas for a more complete look.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/butterfly/butterfly01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/butterfly/butterfly02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper in half by folding the upper left corner to the lower right corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/butterfly/butterfly03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/butterfly/butterfly04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold in half again by folding the upper right corner to the lower left.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/butterfly/butterfly05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/butterfly/butterfly06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Fold in half again by folding the top half back.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/butterfly/butterfly07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/butterfly/butterfly08.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 8\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 8: With your finger, push down on the middle so that it pops in.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue making the origami butterfly.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-butterfly-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/butterfly/origami-butterfly.jpg', 'Origami-Butterfly-Instructions-and-Diagrams', '2021-12-31 18:07:32', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', NULL),
(25, 1, 'How to Make an Origami Butterfly That Flaps', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>How to Make an Origami Butterfly That Flaps</h1>\n</header>\n\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Flapping Butterfly\">Learn how to make an Origami Butterfly with instructions below.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy!</span></div>\n<p>This brilliantly designed origami flapping butterfly by deg farrelly is fun to play with and fortunately, easy to make. The first time I saw this, I was intrigued by its flapping motion and how it appears to gently sit on your fingertips. I immediately began folding it and was surprised to see how something so cool can be so easy to make at the same time. I just had to create instructions for this origami butterfly and share this with you, but not before I designed its wings. Just follow the step by step guide and you\'ll soon know how to make an origami butterfly that can flap its wings.</p>\n<p>P.S. deg farelly recommends folding the flapping butterfly with 8\" to 10\" paper because it flaps better. You can also split the paper in half and fold the butterfly with just a half sheet so that it\'s not so thick. That means you get to have two butterflies instead of one with just one sheet of paper! Thanks for the tip, deg!</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square sheet of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>, color side down. If you only have regular rectangular paper, follow instructions on <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/how-to-make-origami-paper.shtml\">how to make origami paper</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly02-1.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 2-1\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly02-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 2-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Simply fold the bottom half to the top half, making sure the edges meet, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly03-1.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 3-1\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold the top and bottom edges to meet at the center.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly04-1.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 4-1\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold in all four corners so their edges meet at the center horizontal crease.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Fold down the top half.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly06-1.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 6-1\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 6-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Fold the center of the bottom half to the top half. Crease about one inch (2.5 cm) of the center only with your fingernail. Do not crease all the way.<br><br>Remove your finger and there should be a crease in the center only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Butterfly Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Turn the paper over.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue learning how to make an origami butterfly that flaps.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"how-to-make-an-origami-butterfly-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/flapping-butterfly/flapping-butterfly.jpg', 'How-to-Make-an-Origami-Butterfly-That-Flaps', '2021-12-31 18:07:38', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', NULL),
(26, 1, 'How to make an Easy Origami Paper Cat - for Kids', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>How to make an Easy Origami Paper Cat - for Kids</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-cat/easy-origami-cat.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Easy Origami Cat\">Follow the steps below to make this Easy Origami Cat.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy</span></div>\n<p>This easy origami cat is really easy! Kids can have lots of fun folding the cat and drawing in its face. Simply follow the instructions and pictures to make your very own.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-cat/easy-cat01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-cat/easy-cat02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold paper in half by folding the bottom corner to top corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-cat/easy-cat03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold in half again by folding left corner to right corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-cat/easy-cat04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-cat/easy-cat05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Form the ears by folding the left and right corners of the triangle up at an angle, like what you see in the picture.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-cat/easy-cat06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Fold a portion of the top corner down.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-cat/easy-cat07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Turn the figure over.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-cat/easy-cat08.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 8\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 8: Draw some eyes and whiskers!<br><br>Click on \"Like\" below if you like this origami!</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div class=\"shop\"><a href=\"https://shop.origamiway.com/collections/all/cat\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/shop/banner-easy-cat.jpg\"></a></div>\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-cat/easy-origami-cat.jpg', 'How-to-make-an-Easy-Origami-Paper-Cat---for-Kids', '2021-12-31 18:07:46', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', NULL),
(27, 1, 'Origami Cat Instructions and Diagram', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Cat Instructions and Diagram</h1>\n</header>\n  \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/origami-cat.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Cat\"><br>Follow the steps below to make this cool Origami Cat by Eric Ha.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Medium</span></div>\n<p>Wow, this origami cat is one of the best looking I\'ve ever seen that\'s not too difficult to fold. Maybe I\'m biased since I designed it, but it really is pretty. I chose black because black cats are spooky and cool, but also because I need an excuse to use all the black <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a> I have.</p>\n<p>I wouldn\'t consider this origami cat easy if you have no experience at all. In fact, some folds may require a couple of attempts to get right, but they\'re not impossible. You\'ll have fun folding this figure and you\'ll have fun with it after you\'re done.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/cat01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/cat02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper in half by folding the left corner to the right corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/cat03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/cat04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the upper left and right sides to the center as shown.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/cat05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Now fold the bottom left and right sides to the center.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/cat06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Fold in half by folding the bottom corner to the top.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/cat07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Fold most (not all) of the flap back down.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/cat08.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 8\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/cat08-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 8-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 8: Here\'s one of the tricky folds. Open the pocket on the left side and squash down while folding the left side of the triangle to the center.\n<br><br>You may need to adjust the pocket and it\'s okay if it\'s not perfect.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/cat09.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 9\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 9: Do the same to the right side. Now we have a thinner triangle.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue making the origami cat.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-cat-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat/origami-cat.jpg', 'Origami-Cat-Instructions-and-Diagram', '2021-12-31 18:07:55', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', NULL),
(28, 1, 'Make a Paper Dog: Easy Origami Dog Instructions for Kids', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Make a Paper Dog: Easy Origami Dog Instructions for Kids</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-dog/easy-origami-dog.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Easy Origami Dog\">Follow the steps below to make this Easy Origami Dog.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy</span></div>\n<p>Kids will have lots of fun making this easy origami dog. It\'s easy to fold and fun to draw the face on when you\'re done. Just follow the instructions and pictures and you\'ll have your very own easy origami dog!</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-dog/easy-dog01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-dog/easy-dog02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold paper in half by folding the top corner to the bottom corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-dog/easy-dog03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold the triangle in half by folding the left corner to the right corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-dog/easy-dog04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-dog/easy-dog05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Let\'s make the ears! Fold both corners of the triangle down at an angle like you see in the picture.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-dog/easy-dog06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: The head\'s too pointy! Fold the top corner to the back.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-dog/easy-dog07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Unless you want a pointy chin, fold the bottom corner back also.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-dog/easy-dog08.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 8\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 8: Give your dog a face by drawing the eyes and nose!<br><br>Click on \"Like\" below if you like this origami!</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div class=\"shop\"><a href=\"https://shop.origamiway.com/collections/all/dog\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/shop/banner-simple-dog.jpg\"></a></div>\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-dog/easy-origami-dog.jpg', 'Make-a-Paper-Dog:-Easy-Origami-Dog-Instructions-for-Kids', '2021-12-31 18:08:05', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', NULL),
(29, 1, 'Origami Dog Instructions and Diagrams', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Dog Instructions and Diagrams</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog/origami-dog.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Dog\">Follow the steps below to make this cute Origami Dog.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Medium</span></div>\n<p>This is a very cute origami dog that\'s not too hard to make. There are a couple of tricky folds, but I\'ve provided some very good instructions and pictures to guide you. I recommend using two sided <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a> with different colors on each side, that way the ears and nose will be of a different color. That just makes the origami dog cuter and cooler.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog/dog01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog/dog02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper in half by folding the left edge over to the right.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog/dog03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog/dog04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the paper in half again, but this time folding the top edge to the bottom.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog/dog05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Unfold and tilt the paper.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog/dog06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Fold the bottom corner to the center.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog/dog07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Fold the left corner to the center.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue making the origami dog.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-dog-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog/origami-dog.jpg', 'Origami-Dog-Instructions-and-Diagrams', '2021-12-31 18:08:20', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', NULL),
(30, 1, 'Origami Dragon Instructions and Diagram', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Dragon Instructions and Diagram</h1>\n</header>\n\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/origami-dragon-green.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Dragon\">Origami Dragon<br>created by Eric Ha<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Medium</span></div>\n<p>I designed this origami dragon so I may be biased ;), but I have to say that this is one of the coolest looking ones while being one of the easiest to fold. Besides being entirely foldable and not too complex, it can also flap when you pull its tail! It looks awesome, it\'s easy to fold, and you can play with it. You must fold it today!</p>\n<p>The pictures really don\'t do it justice. Yes, there\'s the neat little horned head and cool dragon tail, but the wings stand out above all with it\'s mid flight curvature and gothic form. Fold it and see for yourself how this origami dragon can be so simple, yet so awesome.</p>\n<p>The folds are pretty simple and the pictures are pretty self explanatory. The trickiest fold is probably the wing, but the step by step instructions should guide you through it because it\'s really not hard at all. Read the steps and look at the images carefully and you\'ll get this awesome origami dragon flapping in no time.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper in half by folding the top corner to the bottom corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Now fold the triangle in half by taking the left corner and folding it to the right.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon04-3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Open and spread the top flap, then crease the left and right sides so you can flatten the flap down.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Turn the paper over so we can repeat the last step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon06-3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Make the left flap stand vertically, then open and squash down.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Fold the top layers of both sides to the center.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/dragon08.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 8\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 8: Now fold the top triangle down.\n<br><br>You\'re on your way to making an origami dragon! Go to Next page to continue.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-dragon-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/dragon/origami-dragon-green.jpg', 'Origami-Dragon-Instructions-and-Diagram', '2021-12-31 18:08:28', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', NULL),
(31, 1, 'Make a Paper Elephant: Easy Origami Elephant Instructions', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Make a Paper Elephant: Easy Origami Elephant Instructions</h1>\n</header>\n  \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-origami-elephant.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Easy Origami Elephant\">Follow the steps below to make this Easy Origami Elephant.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy</span></div>\n<p>Learn how to fold an easy origami elephant with very simple step by step photos and instructions. It\'s so easy that even very young kids can make one.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant01.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>. You can also use these colorful <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/printable-origami-paper\">Printable Origami Paper</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant02.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold paper in half by folding the top corner to the bottom corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant03.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Let\'s create a crease in the middle. Fold in half again by folding left corner to right corner, and then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant04.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Now fold the left and right edges of the triangle to the center crease.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant05.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 5\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant05-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 5-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Fold both top corners to the side.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant06.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Fold the left and right corners in like this.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant07.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Turn the figure over.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant08.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 8\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant08-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 8-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 8: Fold up the elephant\'s trunk and fold in back down like this.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant09.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 9\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 9: Keep folding the trunk up and down like an accordian.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant10.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 10\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-elephant10-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 10-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 10: Pull out the elephants trunk and add some eyes.<br><br>Click on \"Like\" below if you like this easy origami elephant!</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-elephant/easy-origami-elephant.jpg', 'Make-a-Paper-Elephant:-Easy-Origami-Elephant-Instructions', '2021-12-31 18:08:34', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', '2021-12-31 18:08:34'),
(32, 1, 'Make a Paper Fish: Easy Origami Fish Instructions and Diagram', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Make a Paper Fish: Easy Origami Fish Instructions and Diagram</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-origami-fish.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Fish\">Follow the instructions below to make this Easy Origami Fish<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy</span></div>\n<p>Kids will have lots of fun folding this easy origami fish and drawing in its eyes and stripes. I doubt they need help at all, but if they do, it would be to collapse the paper into a triangle and folding the fins perfectly. To center the fins perfectly, first place one over the other without creasing. Then kind of roll it up or down till they\'re centered, and crease when they are.</p>\n<p>If this easy origami fish doesn\'t satisfy you, you can try the more challenging <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-fish.shtml\">origami fish</a>. It\'s not an angelfish like this one, but leans towards more of the traditional fish figure. It\'s not too hard, but definitely \"showoffable\".</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make it into a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish02-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the the upper left corner to the lower right corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold the upper right corner to the lower left corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the top half back, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Poke the center with your finger so that the center pops in.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Bring the left and right sides together so that the paper collapses into a triangle.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Rotate the triangle left 90° (counter-clockwise).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish08.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 8\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 8: Fold the bottom corner up a little above the center as shown.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish09.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 9\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 9: Fold the top flap over the bottom one as shown.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-fish10.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 10\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 10: Turn the fish over and you\'re done. Draw the eye and some stripes to make it look nice!<br><br>Click on \"Like\" below if you like this origami!</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div class=\"shop\"><a href=\"https://shop.origamiway.com/collections/all/fish\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/shop/banner-easy-fish.jpg\"></a></div>\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-fish/easy-origami-fish.jpg', 'Make-a-Paper-Fish:-Easy-Origami-Fish-Instructions-and-Diagram', '2021-12-31 18:08:45', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', '2021-12-31 18:08:45'),
(33, 1, 'Origami Fish Instructions and Diagram', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Fish Instructions and Diagram</h1>\n</header>\n\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fish/origami-fish.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Fish\">Follow the instructions below to make this Origami Fish<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Medium</span></div>\n<p>As you can tell, this origami fish is remarkable in its form. However, it looks even better in real life. What you can\'t see here are the gills below the head that causes it to fan out more, thus causing it to generally appear more lifelike than other fish models.</p>\n<p>This origami fish overall is pretty straightforward, but there are a couple of awkward yet simple folds. If you\'re looking for a very <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/easy-origami-fish.shtml\">easy origami fish</a>, click on that link. However, if you\'re looking for one that looks good, but is not too plain or too complex, this one is perfect.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fish/fish01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make it into a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fish/fish02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper in half by folding the left corner to the right corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fish/fish03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold in half again by folding the top corner to the bottom corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fish/fish04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fish/fish04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the left corner to the right edge as shown, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fish/fish05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Fold the upper layer diagonally as shown. Make sure to leave a portion of the right corner unfolded.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fish/fish06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Turn the figure over vertically. The lower left corner of the triangle you touch the crease in the center of the flap. Make adjustments if necessary.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fish/fish07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Fold parts of the triangle down over the lower flap. Your figure should look like this.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue folding the origami fish.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-fish-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n \n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/fish/origami-fish.jpg', 'Origami-Fish-Instructions-and-Diagram', '2021-12-31 18:08:54', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', '2021-12-31 18:08:54'),
(34, 1, 'How to Make an Origami Fox Instructions', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>How to Make an Origami Fox Instructions</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fox/origami-fox.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Fox\">Origami Fox<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy-Medium</span></div>\n<p>This origami fox was requested by Arkive and you can download these instructions by visiting the <a href=\"https://www.arkive.org/education/fun-stuff\">Fun Stuff</a> area. This origami fox is quite easy to make if you follow the pictures and instructions carefully. I apologize for the images being slightly blurry. This is due to taking pictures with a phone in poor lighting.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fox/fox01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fox/fox02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper in half by folding the lower left corner to the upper right corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fox/fox03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold the left corner to the right corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fox/fox04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the bottom corner to the upper right corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fox/fox05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Turn the figure over horizontally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/fox/fox06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Fold the upper right corner to the lower left corner. We\'re almost done!<br><br>Go to Next page to continue making the origami fox.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-fox-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/fox/origami-fox.jpg', 'How-to-Make-an-Origami-Fox-Instructions', '2021-12-31 18:09:03', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', '2021-12-31 18:09:03'),
(35, 1, 'Very Easy Origami Fox', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Very Easy Origami Fox</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/very-easy-fox/very-easy-fox05-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Very Easy Origami Fox\">Follow the steps below to make this Very Easy Origami Fox.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy</span></div>\n<p>This origami fox model is so easy that even very young kids can fold it. They\'ll have a lot of fun making their own fox and drawing in its face. Just follow these step by step photos to learn how to make it.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/very-easy-fox/very-easy-fox01.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>. You can also use these colorful <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/printable-origami-paper\">Printable Origami Paper</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/very-easy-fox/very-easy-fox02.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold paper in half by folding the top corner to the bottom corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/very-easy-fox/very-easy-fox03.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/very-easy-fox/very-easy-fox03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Let\'s make a line in the center. Fold in half again by folding left corner to right corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/very-easy-fox/very-easy-fox04.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/very-easy-fox/very-easy-fox04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the left and right triangle edges toward the center, but not all the way to the center.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/very-easy-fox/very-easy-fox05.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 5\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/very-easy-fox/very-easy-fox05-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 5-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Turn the figure over and draw on the face.<br><br>Click on \"Like\" below if you like this origami!</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/very-easy-fox/very-easy-fox05-2.jpg', 'Very-Easy-Origami-Fox', '2021-12-31 18:09:13', '2022-01-10 13:05:51', '2021-12-31 18:09:13');
