(48, 4, 'How to Make an Origami Box', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>How to Make an Origami Box</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/origami-box.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Box\">Follow the instructions below to make this Origami Box<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Medium</span></div>\n<p>Isn\'t it awesome that a piece of paper can be transformed into a handy dandy origami box with just a few well placed folds? Since it\'s so awesome, it almost appears to be impossible, but let me tell you it\'s totally possible and I\'m going to show to you exactly how it can be done. Afterwards, I\'ll show you how to make a lid for it. After all, what\'s a box without the lid. Yeah baby!</p>\n<p>Just follow the easy step by step instructions and you\'ll be able to make this origami box. It\'s not hard at all, but you\'ll need to look at the pictures carefully to make sure you\'re doing everything correctly.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box02-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper in half from top edge to bottom edge, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold in half again from left to right, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold all four corners to the center.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Rotate the paper so it becomes a square.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Fold the top and bottom edge to the center, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/box07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Unfold the top and bottom triangles.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue learning how to make an origami box.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-box-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/box/origami-box.jpg', 'How-to-Make-an-Origami-Box', '2021-12-31 18:16:22', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:16:22'),
(49, 4, 'Origami Cat Box Instructions', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Cat Box Instructions</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/origami-cat-box.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Cat Box\">Follow the instructions below to make this Origami Cat Box<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Medium</span></div>\n<p>Looking for instructions on how to make a box, but you also happen to be a cat lover? Well I\'ve got the perfect origami to teach you. The origami cat box! Finally you have a cat that can be useful and obedient! I kid, I kid.</p>\n<p>The origami cat box is not difficult to fold at all, and the hardest part is drawing on the face. If you\'re not artistic, your cat will end up unproportioned like mine, but still cute. :3</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>, but if you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box02-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the upper left corner to the lower right corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Now fold the upper right corner to the lower left corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the top half backwards (where the creases meet at an X), then unfold but don\'t flatten it.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: With your finger, poke the center and it should pop in.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Bring the left and right creases to the center to collapse the figure into a triangle.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/cat-box07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Rotate the figure so it\'s upside down.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue with the origami cat box instructions.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-cat-box-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/cat-box/origami-cat-box.jpg', 'Origami-Cat-Box-Instructions', '2021-12-31 18:16:34', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:16:34'),
(50, 4, 'Origami Dog Box Instructions', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Dog Box Instructions</h1>\n</header>\n  \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/origami-dog-box.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Dog Box\">Follow the instructions below to make this Origami Dog Box<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Medium</span></div>\n<p>Don\'t feel like making a plain square box and you also happen to love dogs? Well I\'ve got the perfect solution for your situation. I\'m going to teach you how to make an origami dog box! Woohoo! You\'re welcome.</p>\n<p>The dog box is reasonably easy to fold. There\'s just a couple of \"huh?\" steps, but the pictures should do a wonderful job of helping because <em>I</em> made them. You will need to draw on the dog\'s face so be prepared to display your artistic talents.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>, but if you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box02-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the upper left corner to the lower right corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Now fold the upper right corner to the lower left corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the top half backwards (where the creases meet at an X), then unfold but don\'t flatten it.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: With your finger, poke the center and it should pop in.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Bring the left and right creases to the center to collapse the figure into a triangle.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/dog-box07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Rotate the figure so it\'s upside down.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue with the origami dog box instructions.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-dog-box-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/dog-box/origami-dog-box.jpg', 'Origami-Dog-Box-Instructions', '2021-12-31 18:16:40', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:16:40'),
(51, 4, 'Origami Nik-Nak Box', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Nik-Nak Box</h1>\n</header>\n<iframe src=\"https://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.origamiway.com%2Forigami-nik-nak-box.shtml&amp;layout=standard&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=450&amp;action=like&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=35\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:none; overflow:hidden; width:450px;\" allowtransparency=\"true\"></iframe>\n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/nik-nak-box/nik-nak-box.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Origami Nik-Nak Box\">Follow the instructions below to make this Origami Nik-Nak Box<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Medium</span></div>\n<p>The origami Nik-Nak Box is great for storing all your little nik-naks. Using regular paper is the most convenient way to fold this box, but you can use a more sturdy material to make a nik-nak box that lasts longer. Ready? Just follow the simple instructions to make your own Nik-Nak Box.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/nik-nak-box/01.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Get out a regular sheet of rectangular paper.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/nik-nak-box/02.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the bottom half to the top, making sure the corners touch eatch other.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/nik-nak-box/03.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Once again, fold the bottom half to the top.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/nik-nak-box/04.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the bottom left and right corners to the top.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/nik-nak-box/05.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Fold the left flap to the right along its vertical edge.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/nik-nak-box/06.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 6\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Do the same to the right flap.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/nik-nak-box/07.jpg\" width=\"200\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Unfold both flaps<br><br>Go to Next page to continue with the origami Nik-Nak Box instructions.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-nik-nak-box-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/nik-nak-box/nik-nak-box.jpg', 'Origami-Nik-Nak-Box', '2021-12-31 18:16:44', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:16:44'),
(52, 4, 'Origami Star Box Instructions', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Star Box Instructions</h1>\n</header>\n  \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/origami-star-box.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Star Box\">Follow the instructions below to make this Origami Star Box<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Medium</span></div>\n<p>You are about to learn how to make an origami star box that is both useful and cute. Instead of spending your hard earned money or allowance on a box in the stores, you\'ll know how to make your very own. This box is perfect for your jewelry, coins, paper clips, etc.</p>\n<p>I know it looks difficult, but it\'s actually pretty easy to fold. Just follow the origami star box instructions carefully and you should have no problem making one.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>, but if you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold in half by folding the top corner to the bottom corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold the left corner to the right corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box04-3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Open the top layer so you can squash fold the right corner to the bottom corner as shown in the pictures.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Turn the paper over.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box06-3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Lift the left flap up vertically, then open and squash down like other side.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/star-box07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Rotate the figure so it\'s upside down.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue with the origami star box instructions.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-star-box-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/star-box/origami-star-box.jpg', 'Origami-Star-Box-Instructions', '2021-12-31 18:16:53', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:16:53'),
(53, 4, 'How to Make an Origami Basket with Handle', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>How to Make an Origami Basket with Handle</h1>\n</header>\n  \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/origami-basket.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Basket\">Learn how to make an Origami Basket with instructions below.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy!</span></div>\n<p>Learn how to make an origami basket with handle using these easy to follow instructions. While you can definitely use regular, white, rectangular paper, it\'s best to use square, origami paper with a color or pattern on one side.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square sheet of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>, color side up. If you only have regular rectangular paper, follow instructions on <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/how-to-make-origami-paper.shtml\">how to make origami paper</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 2-1\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket02-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 2-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the left half to the right, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold the top half down.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the top right corner down the center.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Turn the paper over.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 6\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Again, fold the top right corner down the center.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 7-1\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket07-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 7-2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket07-3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 7-3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Open the bottom of the triangle and squash fold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket08.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 8\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 8: Rotate the paper so the opening is on top.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket09.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 9-1\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket09-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 9-2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket09-3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 9-3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 9: Grab the first layer and fold the top half down, crease well, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket10.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 10\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 10: Fold the top corner down to the center.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/basket11.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"How to Make an Origami Basket Step 11\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 11: Fold that top flap down.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue learning how to make an origami basket with handle.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"how-to-make-an-origami-basket-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/basket/origami-basket.jpg', 'How-to-Make-an-Origami-Basket-with-Handle', '2021-12-31 18:17:03', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:17:03'),
(54, 5, 'Make a Paper Rose: Easy Origami Rose Instructions & Diagram', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Make a Paper Rose: Easy Origami Rose Instructions &amp; Diagram</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-origami-rose.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Easy Origami Rose\">Follow the steps below to make this Easy Origami Paper Rose.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy</span></div>\n<p>This easy origami rose is not only beautiful and lifelike, it\'s also remarkably easy to make. Once you get the hang of it, you\'ll be able to whip one out in seconds using pretty much any kind of paper available to you.</p>\n<p>The combination of ease, versatility, and beauty makes the easy origami rose an extremely effective tool for being popular with the ladies. No matter where you are, as long as you have access to a piece of paper or napkin, you have a valuable flirting accessory.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-rose01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a piece of napkin. Regular paper also works, but won\'t look as nice.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-rose02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-rose02-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Roll up the napkin like you see. .</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-rose03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Begin forming the rose by pinching near the top.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-rose04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: While pinching with one hand, Roll below the rose with your other hand.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-rose05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Lift the corner up to one side from the bottom of the napkin.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-rose06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-rose07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Start rolling up from the bottom of the rose.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-rose08.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: As you roll up, try to leave the loose corner hanging to the side. This will be used for the petal.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-rose09.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 8\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 8: Twist the base of the petal so its shape can be more defined. Now it\'s ready to be given away.<br><br>Click on \"Like\" below if you like this origami!</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/easy-rose/easy-origami-rose.jpg', 'Make-a-Paper-Rose:-Easy-Origami-Rose-Instructions-&-Diagram', '2021-12-31 18:17:35', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:17:35'),
(55, 5, 'Origami Flower Stem Instructions and Diagram', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Flower Stem Instructions and Diagram</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/origami-flower-stem.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Flower Stem\">Follow the instructions below to make this Origami Flower Stem<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy-Medium</span></div>\n<p>I was looking for a stem to attach the hydrangea <a href=\"https://origamiway.com/origami-flower.shtml\">origami flower</a>, but couldn\'t find any so I made one myself. Just like the actual hydrangea stems, this origami flower stem will allow you to attach two flowers to it to form a bouquet. Neat huh?</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a> with white side up. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make it into a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem02-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the upper left corner to the lower right corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Now fold the upper right corner to the lower left corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the top half backwards, bending at the \"X\" crease, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Poke the center with your finger so that it pops in.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem06-3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Bring the creases on the side to meet at the center to collapse the paper into a triangle.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Rotate the paper so it\'s upside down.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem08.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 8\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/flower-stem08-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 8-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 8: Fold the triangle in half, then unfold.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-flower-stem-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/flower-stem/origami-flower-stem.jpg', 'Origami-Flower-Stem-Instructions-and-Diagram', '2021-12-31 18:18:36', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:18:36'),
(56, 5, 'Origami Iris Instructions and Diagram', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Iris Instructions and Diagram</h1>\n</header>\n  \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/origami-iris.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Iris\">Follow the steps below to make this Origami Iris.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Medium</span></div>\n<p>There\'s no argument that the origami iris is very pretty. The flower is just so complete and almost lifelike thanks to the well shaped petals and the stamen. The white in the middle of the iris and petal also help bring it to life.</p>\n<p>The origami iris isn\'t really too hard to fold, but you must be able to follow instructions well and remember to use the pictures to help you if you\'re stuck.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/iris01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>, but if you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/iris02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper in half, folding the top corner to bottom corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/iris03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold in half again, folding the left corner to the right corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/iris04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/iris04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/iris04-3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Squash fold the upper layer. To do this, open the flap and squash the right corner to the bottom corner while creasing the sides.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/iris05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Turn the figure over as shown.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/iris06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/iris06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/iris06-3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-3\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Squash fold the left flap as well. To do this, make the left flap stand vertically, then open up and squash down.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue with the origami iris instructions.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-iris-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/iris/origami-iris.jpg', 'Origami-Iris-Instructions-and-Diagram', '2021-12-31 18:18:49', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:18:49'),
(57, 5, 'Origami Kusudama Flower Instructions', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Kusudama Flower Instructions</h1>\n</header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Kusudama Flower\">Follow the steps below to make this Origami Kusudama Flower.<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy-Medium</span></div>\n<p>The origami kusudama flower is undeniably beautiful and appears complex and difficult to make, but surprisingly there are only a few steps to it. However, you do need a total of five pieces of paper because this flower is actually made up of five petals. Each petal is made with one sheet of paper. This means you will also need glue. Ready? Let\'s get started.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a> with color side down, but if you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper into a triangle by folding the bottom corner to the top corner.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower03-1.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold the triangle into a diamond by folding the left and right corners to the top.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower04-1.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Take the flaps you just folded and fold them outward to the left and right edges of the diamond.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower05-1.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower05-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5-2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower05-3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5-3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower05-4.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5-4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Unfold the left side and insert a finger into the pocket of that flap, then squash down as shown.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Repeat step 5 for the right side as well so that you have two squashed sides.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue with the origami kusudama flower instructions.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-kusudama-flower-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/kusudama-flower/kusudama-flower.jpg', 'Origami-Kusudama-Flower-Instructions', '2021-12-31 18:18:56', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:18:56'),
(58, 6, 'How to make an origami heart', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>How to make an origami heart</h1>\n</header>\n  \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/origami-heart.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Heart\">Follow the instructions below to make this Origami Heart<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy</span></div>\n<p>If you\'re trying to learn how to make an origami heart, this diagram will teach you in just one page. There\'s nothing like a handmade gift to bring joy to the special someone in your life. That special someone can be a spouse, a sibling, your parents, or a good friend, whomever it may be, they\'ll be happy that you spent a little time and effort on them.</p>\n<p>If you enjoy making this origami heart, check out the other <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-hearts.shtml\">origami hearts</a> available.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/heart01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a> with white side up. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make it into a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/heart02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/heart02-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper in half by folding the top corner to the bottom corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/heart03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/heart03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Fold the left corner to the right corner, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/heart04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: Fold the top corner to the center.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/heart05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Fold the bottom corner to the top edge.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/heart06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/heart06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Fold the bottom left and right edges to the center crease.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/heart07.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 7\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 7: Fold the top and side corners back.<br><br>Now you know how to make an origami heart! Easy wasn\'t it?</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div class=\"shop\"><a href=\"https://shop.origamiway.com/collections/all/heart\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/shop/banner-heart.jpg\"></a></div>\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart/origami-heart.jpg', 'How-to-make-an-origami-heart', '2021-12-31 18:19:45', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:19:45'),
(59, 6, 'Origami Heart Bookmark Instructions and Diagram', NULL, '\n<header class=\"major\">\n\n<h1>Origami Heart Bookmark Instructions and Diagram</h1>\n </header>\n \n<div id=\"final\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/origami-heart-bookmark.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Origami Heart Bookmark\">Follow the instructions below to make this Origami Heart Bookmark<br><span class=\"difficulty\">Difficulty: Easy-Medium</span></div>\n<p>The origami heart bookmark is a remarkable piece of paper art. It is best made using <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a> with different colors on each side, such as white and red. The different colors allow the heart to stand out from the base of the bookmark. However, if all you have is plain white paper, don\'t let that stop you from being creative. You\'ll have a plain canvas to put your artistic talent to work using crayons and color pencils.</p>\n<p>This origami heart bookmark is pretty easy to fold. There\'s just a couple of squash like folds that\'s required, but the rest is fairly simple.</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark01.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 1\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 1: Start with a square piece of <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/origami-paper.shtml\">origami paper</a>. If you only have regular 8.5x11 paper, follow these instructions to <a href=\"https://www.origamiway.com/make-origami-paper.shtml\">make it into a square sheet</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark02.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark02-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 2-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 2: Fold the paper in half, left over to the right, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark03.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark03-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 3-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 3: Cut the paper in half. We just need one half.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark04.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark04-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 4-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 4: With one half, fold that in half and unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark05.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark05-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 5-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 5: Fold the sides to the center, then unfold.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"diagram\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark06.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/heart-bookmark06-2.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"149\" alt=\"Step 6-2\"></td>\n<td class=\"alignTop\">Step 6: Fold the upper right corner down to the crease as shown, then unfold.<br><br>Go to Next page to continue folding the origami heart envelope.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<div align=\"center\" id=\"origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\">\n<script data-cfasync=\"false\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n    freestar.queue.push(function () { googletag.display(\'origamiway_728x90_970x90_320x50_unit_5\'); });\n</script>\n</div>\n<div id=\"next\"><a href=\"origami-heart-bookmark-2.shtml\"><img src=\"https://www.origamiway.com/images/page-next.png\"></a></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.origamiway.com/images/heart-bookmark/origami-heart-bookmark.jpg', 'Origami-Heart-Bookmark-Instructions-and-Diagram', '2021-12-31 18:19:55', NULL, '2021-12-31 18:19:55');
